meta.name: PostgreSQL
meta.description: Dashboard for the telegraf input plug-in: PostgreSQL
meta.author: InfluxData

cells.note: This dashboard gives you an overview of metrics from PostgreSQL on each host and includes metrics from `postgresql` set of measurements populated by the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input Plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: PostgresSQL - Buffers

queries.query: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("buffers_alloc"),10s) AS "alloc", non_negative_derivative(mean("buffers_backend"),10s) AS "backend" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host = :host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("buffers_alloc"),10s) AS "alloc", non_negative_derivative(mean("buffers_backend"),10s) AS "backend" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host = :host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: Postgres deadlocks/conflicts

queries.query: SELECT mean("deadlocks") AS "deadlocks", mean("conflicts") AS "conflicts" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT mean("deadlocks") AS "deadlocks", mean("conflicts") AS "conflicts" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: PostgreSQL commit/rolback per sec

queries.query: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("xact_commit"),1s) AS "commit", non_negative_derivative(mean("xact_rollback"),1s) AS "rollback" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host = :host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("xact_commit"),1s) AS "commit", non_negative_derivative(mean("xact_rollback"),1s) AS "rollback" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE host = :host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: PostgreSQL rows in / sec

queries.query: SELECT  non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_inserted"),1s) AS "inserted", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_updated"),1s) AS "updated", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_deleted")) AS "deleted" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host" = :host: GROUP BY time(:interval:)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT  non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_inserted"),1s) AS "inserted", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_updated"),1s) AS "updated", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_deleted")) AS "deleted" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host" = :host: GROUP BY time(:interval:)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: PostgreSQL rows out / sec

queries.query: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_fetched"),1s) AS "fetched", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_returned"),1s) AS "returned" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE "host"=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_fetched"),1s) AS "fetched", non_negative_derivative(mean("tup_returned"),1s) AS "returned" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."postgresql" WHERE "host"=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf PostgreSQL Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/postgresql).

cells.name: Processes

queries.query: SELECT mean("total") AS "mean_total" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."processes" WHERE  host=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT mean("total") AS "mean_total" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."processes" WHERE  host=:host: AND time > :dashboardTime: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf Processes Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/processes).

cells.name: CPU Usage

queries.query: SELECT mean("usage_system") AS "system", mean("usage_user") as "user", mean("usage_idle") as "idle"  FROM ":db:".":rp:"."cpu" WHERE host = :host: and time > :dashboardTime: AND "cpu"='cpu-total' GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT mean("usage_system") AS "system", mean("usage_user") as "user", mean("usage_idle") as "idle"  FROM ":db:".":rp:"."cpu" WHERE host = :host: and time > :dashboardTime: AND "cpu"='cpu-total' GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf CPU Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/cpu).

cells.name: Filesystems usage

queries.query: SELECT mean("used_percent") AS "used" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."disk" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host"=:host: GROUP BY time(:interval:), "path" FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT mean("used_percent") AS "used" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."disk" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host"=:host: GROUP BY time(:interval:), "path" FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the [Telegraf Disk Input plugin](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/disk).

queries.query: SELECT mean("total") AS "total", mean("used") AS "used" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."swap" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host"=:host: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT mean("total") AS "total", mean("used") AS "used" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."swap" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host"=:host: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.name: System Load

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_recv"), 1s) AS "recieved", non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_sent"), 1s) AS "sent" FROM ":db:".":rp:"."net" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "host" = :host: GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)
